  "prompt": "How does GST Bill will work?",
  "response": "The Goods and Services Tax (GST) is a comprehensive indirect tax that replaced multiple cascading taxes in India. Here's how the GST Bill works:\n\n1. Unified Tax Structure\n- Single tax across India\n- Replaces multiple state and central taxes\n- Simplifies tax collection and compliance\n\n2. Tax Rates\n- Multiple tax slabs: 0%, 5%, 12%, 18%, and 28%\n- Essential items have lower rates\n- Luxury and sin goods have higher rates\n\n3. Input Tax Credit\n- Businesses can claim credit for taxes paid on inputs\n- Reduces tax cascading\n- Promotes transparency in tax payment\n\n4. Registration\n- Mandatory for businesses with annual turnover above \u20b940 lakhs\n- Online registration process\n- Unique GST Identification Number (GSTIN)\n\n5. Filing Returns\n- Monthly and quarterly returns\n- Online filing through GST portal\n- Input tax credit reconciliation\n\n6. Inter-State Transactions\n- Uniform tax rates\n- Simplified movement of goods\n- Reduced transportation costs\n\n7. Destination-Based Taxation\n- Tax collected at consumption point\n- Reduces tax burden on manufacturing states\n\n8. Composition Scheme\n- Simplified tax compliance for small businesses\n- Lower tax rates for smaller enterprises\n\n9. Electronic Way Bill (E-Way Bill)\n- Mandatory for goods transportation\n- Reduces tax evasion\n- Tracks movement of goods",
